##The direct online reporting system for infectious diseases cost $730 million. Why did it fail for 28 days?

I-CAIJING

Linkage of three medical, bridge capital, direct health

After January 24,2020, the Infectious Disease Network direct report system is very important to report and summarize the information of epidemic situation in different places, and to prevent and control the epidemic situation as a whole, but still needs to further improve the reporting mechanism, the monitoring system is too complicated and so on

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wen | CAIJING special correspondent Wuhan Xinna, Wang Xiao Caijing correspondent Sun Aimin, Xin Ying

Editor | Wang Xiao

A number of medical experts reviewed the success and failure of the work in the early days of the outbreak, and both mentioned that after the SARS epidemic in 2003, the "direct network reporting system for infectious diseases" established by the central and local governments at great expense did not play a full role.

On December 27,2019, the Hubei Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital reported the first case of pneumonia of unknown cause orally to the Kong Hon district CDC in Wuhan. Three days later, the medical administration and Medical Administration Department of the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission issued an urgent notice to all medical institutions in the city, "All units are requested to immediately check and count the pneumonia patients of unknown origin with similar characteristics who have been seen for nearly a week and submit the statistical form (the scanned stamp) to the mailbox of the Medical Administration Office of the Municipal Health Commission by 4 p.m. Today. "

28 days later, on January 24,2020, the day after Wuhan was "sealed off" , china Center for Disease Control and Prevention (CCDC)"infectious disease network direct reporting system COVID-19 pneumonia dynamic monitoring function" online.

This new function is based on the National Information System for monitoring infectious diseases and Public Health Emergencies (hereinafter referred to as the direct reporting system on the Internet) , which was established in China after the SARS epidemic in 2003 with a joint investment of about 730 million yuan by the central and local governments, rapid reporting of COVID-19 pneumonia cases, diagnosis and treatment, source of infection, etc. .

On January 20, the COVID-19, with the approval of the State Council, included pneumonia contracted by infected persons in Category B Infectious Diseases as stipulated in the law on the prevention and control of infectious diseases, and adopted measures for the prevention and Control of Category A infectious diseases.

This is an important node. According to the relevant regulations, category B Infectious Diseases are managed according to Category A, and the cases are required to be reported online within 2 hours after discovery. For the reported information, it is necessary to complete the three-level confirmation audit within 2 hours.

But before January 24, the new function comes online, the network direct report system did not give full play to its due function. People infected with the new coronavirus in most places, including Wuhan, the epicenter of the outbreak, reported the outbreak by word of mouth, email and telephone over a 28-day period. Or Rather, the direct reporting system failed during the first 28 days of the outbreak.

"It can not be said that it has not played a role, at least after January 24,2020, that is, after the level I response in Hubei Province, to report and summarize the information of the epidemic in various places, and this system is very important for the overall prevention and control of the epidemic, " Xu Xiaoyuan, a member of the Expert Group of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention and a physician in charge of the Infectious Diseases Department of the Peking University First Hospital, told Caijing.

Oral report, email report and online direct report

A 65-year-old man with fever shows no signs of improvement after doctors at Wuhan Central Hospital exhausted routine treatment and examinations on December 24,2019. The suspicious doctor takes a sample from the patient and sends it to a third-party testing facility for genetic testing.

Three days later (December 27,2019) , the testing agency "did not dare to give a written report" , only to inform Wuhan Central Hospital by telephone that the test result was "coronavirus, unclassified" , "There is no written report, " a staff member of the hospital's emergency department told CAIJING. "You can't report it. What you say doesn't count. "

It is reported that the Wuhan Central Hospital of this suspected case did not report the direct reporting system. On the day they received the oral results of the test samples, Zhang Jixian, director of the respiratory and Critical Care Medicine Department of the Hubei Integrated Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital, treated several patients with similar symptoms in succession, and all of them ruled out the infection of known common pathogens, the patient's condition was reported to the hospital leadership, the hospital sentiment office and the medical department, and the hospital then orally reported to the Kong Hon District CDC in Wuhan.

A Gansu CDC official told Caijing that the oral report can not be considered a formal report, just like hearsay, and CDC staff can not catch wind of this investigation. But as soon as a standard report is prepared, the CDC will conduct an investigation to find the In & Out.

After the SARS epidemic in 2003, China established a direct online reporting system for infectious diseases, so that patients with infectious diseases or suspected infectious diseases can be quickly reported and examined in hospitals, the health department and the disease control system can also quickly analyze and determine the epidemic situation. According to the design plan, this huge information system theoretically covers the whole country horizontally, vertically "to the township health center computer can see this network system. ".

The procedure is that once a front-line health care worker discovers an infectious case, pneumonia of unknown cause, he or she fills out a paper or electronic infectious disease report card and finally collects it to the Public Health Department or hospital-related Department of the hospital, these departments are responsible for recording cases into the direct reporting system.

Direct reporting system uses a dedicated network system, real-time cases can be reported directly to China's CDC Data Center, CDC has a dedicated person to monitor these cases data.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
However, a number of first-line clinical doctors to "CAIJING" reporter, direct reporting system complex, many doctors have not been trained, do not know how to use effectively.

At the beginning of January 2020, Wuhan issued the Emergency Monitoring Plan for the viral pneumonia of unknown causes in Wuhan, which includes how to report cases: for cases that can not be clearly diagnosed, infectious disease report cards should be filled in immediately, "unexplained viral pneumonia" and a direct online bulletin.

Direct reporting system has "unexplained pneumonia" subset. "CAIJING" reporters were issued a "new crown pneumonia diagnosis and treatment and prevention and control of the program, " said, still can not rule out suspected cases of direct network report by medical institutions, disease selection "unknown cause pneumonia.

On January 15, the National Health Commission began training provincial and municipal medical institutions on how to screen suspected cases and use a direct reporting system. Three days later, in an internal training session at the Wuhan Union Hospital, medical staff were required to report directly online within two hours if they found a patient who met the definition of an observed case. Direct Network Disease Species Selection "human infection COVID-19" , to "observe the case" type report.

CAIJING reporters in the interview found that direct online reporting is not really in the front line is effectively implemented, even in the outbreak center in Wuhan.

Three kilometers away from the Wuhan Union Hospital, a staff member at a provincial hospital told Caijing that before January 20, the Public Health Department of his hospital had reported only suspected cases to the local health commission and the CDC. Previously, the hospital found more than a dozen suspected cases did not report directly in the network.

Until January 30, the suspected patients were still notified by telephone to the Health Commission and the Center for Disease Control and Prevention, the head of a designated hospital in Yunnan for new pneumonia told CAIJING.

Another approach actually bypasses the direct reporting system: a clinician at Wuhan Zhongnan Hospital restored the hospital's direct reporting system to a CAIJING reporter. He disclosed that before the encounter of pneumonia of unknown cause, the clinician first reported to the director, the director reported to the Dean, the Dean reported to the report. Hospitals don't report to the national level through the system, they report to the city or the province. Moreover, the clinical judgment will show that the diagnosis is pending, the computer system can not directly identify, and therefore can not report directly.

A staff member of the Kong Hon District Center for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) in Wuhan, who is in charge of the Infectious Disease Report Card Review, corroborated this statement. He told Caijing that the initial hospitals may have reported the disease orally to the CDC leadership, but did not fill in in the Infectious Disease Network direct report system, reports.

On December 29,2019, two days after reporting the case to the Kong Hon Center for Disease Control and Prevention, Zhang Jixian's Hubei Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital organized an expert consultation and reported directly to the Hubei Provincial Health Commission and Wuhan Municipal Health Commission.

The next day (December 30,2019) , after receiving a report from Wuhan Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital, the Medical Administration and Medical Administration Department of Wuhan Health Commission issued an urgent notice, all medical institutions are required to immediately check and count the unidentified pneumonia patients with similar characteristics who have been seen for nearly a week, and scan the statistical form before 4:00 pm on the same day, and submit it to the mailbox of the medical administration and Medical Management Office of the Municipal Health Commission.

Around 1 p.m. on December 31,2019, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission announced that 27 cases have been found, of which 7 cases are in serious condition. The cases, which were supposed to have come in a notification e-mail from the district's hospitals the day before, were the first official notification of the outbreak in the disaster.

Neither Zhang Jixian, nor the hospital, and to the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission Medical Administration Department to the hospital's emergency notice, there is no mention of direct network reporting system. In other words, in the early days of the epidemic, until the new features of the direct reporting system out of the 28 days, the direct reporting system is equivalent to being bypassed.

Takatomi, director of the Chinese CDC, told the Boao Forum for Asia in 2019 that, "China has a very robust information system, and the health authorities will be aware of any suspicious cases, including new or re-emerging infectious diseases, within six hours, because we have established a direct information reporting system covering the whole country. "

Why don't you just report it online?

The direct online reporting system for infectious diseases was set up in 2003 at the time of SARS, and was completed in 2004, with co-financing from the central government (250 million yuan) and local governments (480 million yuan) . These investments cover system hardware and software, network access, staff training, and programmer salaries.

The hospital pays 1300 yuan a year for the Unicom direct report system. There are six subsystems under the direct reporting system, official infectious system, public health emergency reporting system, Special Disease Management System, hospital death case reporting system, health risk factors reporting system, disease prevention and Control Basic Information System.

The requirement is to observe and report abnormal events on a daily basis so that outbreaks can be reported to the national level as soon as possible. For example, if a doctor finds a case of SARS, he or she can write it directly under Class B SARS in the Official infectious.

"Any doctor who diagnoses an infectious disease must fill out an infectious disease report card and report it to the hospital's Department of Prevention and protection, which in turn reports it to the CDC without any omissions or delays. In fact, there is no paper report card and the report should be reported directly online, but to avoid mistakes, doctors often first take a picture of his diagnosis and send it to the Department of Prevention and protection, and the Department of Prevention and protection will send the report directly online on behalf of the department."A staff member from the Sensory Control Department of a Shanghai Hospital told Caijing.

However, by January 20,2020, NPV PNEUMONIA was a new disease that had not yet been recognized as a "Official infectious" and therefore was not part of the Official infectious in the system and could not be uploaded to the Official infectious.

The system also has a direct report for Pneumonia of Unknown origin (Pue) , which is where doctors are required to report cases of Pneumonia of Unknown origin if they meet certain criteria. Officials initially called the detected cases in Wuhan "viral pneumonia of unknown origin. ".

Feng Zijian, deputy director of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, wrote in the journal disease surveillance in 2017 that if the current case definition required doctors to report pneumonia of unknown cause, "there will be a lot of cases, not only will increase the workload of clinicians and CDC staff, but also easy to cause a waste of public health resources. ".

The Department of Health has four definitions of "pneumonia of unknown cause" : fever, armpit temperature 38 C, imaging features of pneumonia, low or normal white blood cell count in the early stage of onset, or low lymphocyte classification count; After 3-5 days of Standard Antibiotic Treatment, the disease did not improve significantly or showed progressive aggravation.

The Medical Institution shall, within 12 hours after the discovery of the cases in accordance with the above-mentioned four articles, organize a group of experts from this unit to conduct consultation and examination. Still can not be clearly diagnosed, should immediately fill in the infectious disease report card, marked "unexplained pneumonia" and direct report to the Disease Control System Network.

Wuhan, a third-tier hospital, breathing doctor said to the "CAIJING" reporter: "If you do not understand what is the reason, how can it be reported through the direct reporting system? "

The reporting mechanism of the disease prevention and control system is territorial vertical, management classification, divided into national level, local level, county level and township level, the Centers for Disease Control and prevention at all levels and the health administration at the same level for information communication and feedback. The Wuhan Central Hospital and the Integrated Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital are both in the Kong Hon District of Wuhan.

If the Kong HON CDC records hospital-reported cases into the direct reporting system, only Wuhan, Hubei and the National CDC can see, other provinces can not see Hubei Information.

The industry rule is, "generally first oral report, because the written report needs a process, " Hubei Integrated Hospital of Traditional Chinese and Western medicine staff told the "finance and economics" reporter.

The above-mentioned staff member in charge of Infectious Disease Report Card Audit at Kong Hon district CDC in Wuhan confirmed this statement to Caijing reporter. Although infectious disease outbreaks are reported from the bottom up, for these new diseases, if you want to report through the system, first by the Higher Disease Control Departments, health departments organized expert consultation, and other experts to determine the disease, the following medical institutions can report through the disease control direct reporting system.

"The process of monitoring and reporting is so complex that there is a lot of pressure on both reporting and processing, with the need for step-by-step screening, sampling and monitoring. Moreover, the system was originally designed to monitor SARS and human bird flu, and it has not happened in so many years, so medical institutions have generally taken it for granted, even though the CDC conducts annual training for its disease control staff and hospitals, which is almost a formality,"a CDC doctor told Caijing.

Another reason is that, "when a pathogen is detected in a hospital, the system goes straight out of the notification box. But if you entrust the pathogens to other testing companies outside the hospital, the report box won't jump out of the system,"said a suction doctor at a Sanjia Hospital in Wuhan, at this time it is impossible to fill in the computer system, the need for manual reporting, the General First Report to the hospital sensory control section.

Therefore, although the CDC has a dedicated person to monitor the direct reporting system data, every two hours must log on to the system to patrol, based on case data to make corresponding response, but at the source of the report is a step backward.

"I didn't know there was a system. "

On February 22,2020, Caijing reporters interviewed six doctors from the third-level hospitals in Wuhan, all of whom said they had not heard of the reporting system for pneumonia of unknown cause and had never used it in practice.

The original intention of the central and local governments to set up the direct reporting system at great expense, as the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention said when introducing the system, to make up for "in 2003, a sudden SARS epidemic disaster, exposed China's Public Health Information System Development Lag, information, slow decision-making, poor command and other weak links. ".

China first reported three confirmed human cases of H7N9 avian influenza on March 31,2013, according to an article on the official website of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, from active surveillance. Of the first 3 cases reported, 1 was detected by the pneumonia surveillance system of unknown origin and 2 by the National Surveillance System for major infectious diseases.

However, according to a 2017 paper by Feng Zijian, Xiang Nijuan and others, a study of unexplained pneumonia surveillance systems in two top three hospitals in Anhui Province found that of the 2,619 cases of acute respiratory tract infection in both hospitals, of the 335 cases that met the criteria for pneumonia of unknown origin, only one was reported to the local CDC.

A survey of tube-bed doctors who failed to report cases that met the definition of PUE found that 76 per cent were unaware of the work of monitoring pneumonia of unknown origin and 53 per cent did not understand the definition of PUE.

"The monitoring of pneumonia of unknown cause is so inefficient in local hospitals that one year we found eight cases of pneumonia of unknown cause that met the definition of pneumonia in the inpatient system of two hospitals in a municipality. These eight cases were not reported. At that time, there were only eight cases reported in more than 260 medical institutions in the city. This means more cases are not being reported at all,"said the CDC doctor.

In the 2017 paper, Feng suggested that changes to existing surveillance programmes should be considered, such as adding epidemiological risk factor exposure conditions to the existing PUE case definition to increase the specificity of the case definition, reduce the reporting pressure on clinicians to improve compliance with the operational process requirements of the monitoring programme.

A member of the Expert Group of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention made an analysis to a reporter from CAIJING, "In the early days of the NCP epidemic, this direct reporting system had little effect. After all, it was a new virus that even experts could not be sure of, and even grassroots receiving hospitals and disease control departments could not understand it. The symptoms were similar to other pneumonia and even to influenza. "

According to a report forwarded on the official website of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention on August 5,2019, the direct online reporting system now covers all disease prevention and control institutions at and above the county level nationwide, it also covers 98 per cent of county-level medical institutions and 96 per cent of township health centres.

February 23,2020, sentence is too long, please supply a shorter sentence

How the new features make it easier to walk

On the third day of the first lunar month (January 27,2020) , Xu Yucai, deputy director of the health bureau in Shanyang County, Shaanxi Province, about 600 kilometers from Wuhan, realized that his work rhythm would have to be adjusted again.

On that day, the fourth trial edition of the COVID-19 was released, requiring medical staff to consider a suspected case after finding one that meets the definition of the case, and to consider the suspected case after consultation by an expert in the hospital or by the attending physician, i want a live feed in two hours.

This means that the diagnostic authority for suspected cases has been delegated. "Once experts from ordinary hospitals and even a few doctors from hospitals have discussed the cases, they can report them directly, " Xu Yucai told CAIJING, before the screening of new coronary pneumonia more stringent requirements, suspected cases must be through the county-level expert consultation, evaluation before reporting in the disease control direct reporting system.

At this point, the cases of NCP are directly reported to the Infectious Disease Network reporting system NCP dynamic monitoring function. The whole CDC system will be able to see it.

This function was launched on January 24, and can realize the rapid reporting of new pneumonia case information, diagnosis and treatment information, infection source and other related information. However, after the operation of the new system, the hospital for online direct report at the same time, there are also calls to inform the district CDC for the record;

"there are too many kinds of surveillance systems in hospitals, including influenza surveillance, respiratory tract infection surveillance, and Official infectious surveillance. The definitions and clinical features of these diseases cross each other. In addition to Official infectious surveillance, most of the time, doctors at the grassroots level can only do more than one thing at a time, " a staff member who is assisting a municipal disease control department in northwest China told Caijing.

On January 25, the CDC and the COVID-19 dispatched staff to various places to train the newly launched pneumonia dynamic surveillance system.

Send the national team to the local, the Organization of video training sessions, general training a more than 1 hour, mainly explain the new system to report the process, technical maintenance.

The aid worker of the above-mentioned Disease Control Department told Caijing that the local disease control staff and doctors were completely unaware of the unknown pneumonia monitoring system, "fortunately, there is now a new pneumonia network direct reporting system, or can only phone to the higher-level daily report, fill in various forms. ".
